==English==

===Etymology===
Dutch ''ranten'' 'talk nonsense, rave'.

===Pronunciation===

{{US}} ([[SAMPA]]): [r{nt]

===Noun===
'''rant'''

# A criticism done by ranting.

===Verb===
'''to rant'''

# To speak or shout at length in an uncontrollable anger.
# To criticize by ranting.

